---

**The core question**

What becomes impossible to see when algorithms enter organizational life — not as tools?

AI systems carry implicit theories about collective organizing. These theories are invisible from inside. The pressure to converge — in models, in institutions, in how people use these tools — prunes possibilities without leaving a trace. The loss feels like clarity.

